Police in Elgeyo Marakwet and West Pokot are pursuing bandits behind border attacks. Kerio Valley deputy county commissioner James Chacha (pictured) yesterday said security agencies have received a list of the suspected bandits. Two people from Elgeyo Marakwet and West Pokot were shot dead in two cattle rustling attacks in Kamolokon on Monday and Tuesday. Chacha said local state administrators have been directed to help with the arrests.